##
# readline -
# $Header$
##

= shortcuts =
 * C-b: Move back one character
 * C-f: Move foward one character
 * C-d: Delete the character underneath the cursor
 * C-_, C-x, C-u: undo the last editing command
 * C-a: move to the start of the line
 * C-e: move to the end of the line
 * M-f: move forward a word
 * M-b: move backware a word
 * C-l: clear the screen, reprinting the current line at the top
 * C-k: kill the text from the current cursor position to the end of the line
 * M-d: kill from the cursor to the end of the current word
 * M-<DEL>: kill from the cursor to the start of the current word
 * C-w: kill from the cursor to the previous whitspace
 * C-y: Yank the most recently killed text back into the buffer at the cursor
 * M-y: rotate the kill, and yank the new top
 * C-P: previous history
 * C-n: next history
 * M-<: begin of history
 * M->: end of history
 * C-r: reverse search history
 * C-s: forward search history
 * M-., M-_: yank last arg



